excerpt: Jain temple lavishly decorated with glass mosaics & chandeliers, plus an onyx Mahavira statue.
detail_description: Kanch Mandir, also known as the Temple of Glass, is a Jain temple in Indore, India. Built by Seth Hukumchand in 1903, this lavish temple is entirely covered in glass panels and mosaic artwork. The interiors are adorned with intricate glass mosaics, chandeliers, and an onyx statue of Mahavira.
name: Kanch Mandir
address: Kaanch Mandir, Pasari Bhavan, Opposite Kaanch Mandir, Itwaria Bazaar, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452002, India

excerpt: Lavish 19th-century palace of the Holkar dynasty, in a mix of baroque, rococo & neoclassical styles.
detail_description: Lal Bagh Palace, a lavish 19th-century mansion of the Holkar dynasty, showcases a blend of baroque, rococo, and neoclassical architectural styles. This three-story palace has been transformed into a grand museum featuring Italian and Indian paintings, exquisite chandeliers, and furnishings reflecting early Georgian and late Persian designs. Spanning across 28 hectares of land, it stands as a testament to the opulence and culture of the Maratha kingdom.
name: Lal Bagh Palace
address: PR2W+2RH, Nai Duniya, Revenue Colony, Indira Gandhi Nagar, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452007, India

excerpt: Small place with historical artifacts, including Parmar & medieval sculptures, plus coins & weapons.
detail_description: Step into the Central Museum in Indore and take a journey through time, exploring over 10,000 rare artifacts that span from prehistoric fossils to medieval sculptures. The museum showcases the rich cultural heritage of the region with diverse galleries and intriguing displays. After marveling at antique swords and stone-carved jharokhas from royal times, relax at the cafe before continuing your exploration.
name: Central Museum, Indore
address: PV4H+3HW, Near GPO Square, Residency, Navlakha, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452001, India

excerpt: Landmark church from 1858, with ornate, split-level facades & spires topped by red-tiled roofs.
detail_description: The White Church in Indore is a significant landmark, dating back to 1858 and showcasing ornate split-level facades and spires topped by red-tiled roofs. Constructed with the support of Sir Robert North Hamilton, the then Governor General of India, this colonial structure near the Maharajah's palace Rajwada reflects British influence prior to independence. Designed by British engineer Ross McMahon, it features a simple European style with turrets and large windows.
name: White Church (Indore)
address: Pipliyahana Rd, White Church Colony, Residency Area, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452001, India

excerpt: Imposing 1700s 7-storey palace from the Holkar dynasty, with a blend of Maratha & European styles.
detail_description: Rajwada Palace, a magnificent 7-storey structure built by the Holkar dynasty in the 1700s, showcases a fusion of Maratha, Mughal, and European architectural styles. Recently renovated, it stands as a historic masterpiece with intricate detailing and spacious courtyards. The palace hosts grand festivals and is surrounded by bustling markets.
name: Rajwada Palace
address: Rajwada, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452002, India

excerpt: Lush reserve hosting a wide range of exotic birds & other wildlife in sprawling, verdant surrounds.
detail_description: Ralamandal Wildlife Sanctuary, established in 1981, is one of the oldest sanctuaries in Madhya Pradesh. Spanning five square kilometers, it is a lush paradise for nature lovers with diverse flora and fauna. The sanctuary boasts a rich biodiversity with plants like bamboo, teak, eucalyptus, saja, and babool. Visitors can explore the sanctuary by car or bike and enjoy camel rides.
name: Ralamandal Wildlife Sanctuary
address: Mirjapur, Madhya Pradesh 452020, India

detail_description: Annapurna Temple, located in Indore, is a renowned pilgrimage center dedicated to Goddess Annapurna, the deity of food. This sacred site also houses shrines for Sivan, Hanuman, and Kalabhairava. The temple's serene environment makes it an ideal place for spiritual reflection and peace. Constructed with beautiful marble stones, it offers a tranquil and pleasant atmosphere for visitors seeking solace. Additionally, the premises include other temples worth exploring during your visit.
name: Annapurna Temple
address: Annapurna Rd, Annapurna Mandir, Vinay Nagar, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452020, India

detail_description: Rajwada is located in a bustling area with easy access to various neighborhoods and landmarks such as Nipania, Vijay Nagar, Khandwa Road, A B Road, and many more. This prime location offers convenience for visitors to explore the city's attractions and make the most of their time. Whether it's for special occasions or simply cherishing life's moments, Rajwada provides a central hub for experiencing all that the surrounding areas have to offer.
name: Rajwada
address: Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452004, India

excerpt: Hindu temple dating from 1875 dedicated to Ganesh & featuring several shrines on the grounds.
detail_description: Khajrana Ganesh Mandir is a Hindu temple in Indore, dating back to 1875 and dedicated to Lord Ganesh. It was built by Ahilyabai Holkar to protect the idol from Aurangzeb. The temple features a Ganesha statue and smaller shrines for other deities. The idol is made of various materials, and the Garbhagriha has intricate paintings depicting Indian festivals.
name: Khajrana Ganesh Mandir
address: Ganeshpuri Main Rd, Ganeshpuri, Khajrana, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452016, India

detail_description: Chappan Dukan is a famous food and shopping area in Indore, India. It is known for its 56 shops that offer a variety of street food, snacks, sweets, and local delicacies. The bustling atmosphere and the aroma of delicious food make it a popular destination for locals and tourists alike. Visitors can sample a wide range of culinary delights, from spicy chaat to mouthwatering desserts.
name: Chappan Dukan
address: New Palasia, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452001, India

excerpt: Temple for its 25-foot monumental idol of Ganesh, circa 1875 & considered the largest in the world.
detail_description: Bada Ganpati Temple, located in a bustling neighborhood west of the Kanch Mandir, is home to a 25-foot tall idol of Lord Ganesh. This monumental statue was installed in 1875 and is believed to be the largest of its kind in the world. The temple's significance lies not only in its modest appearance but also in the sheer size of the idol.
name: Bada Ganpati
address: Malharganj, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452002, India

excerpt: Art & culture exhibitions in a 1904 hall with elaborate Indo-Gothic windows, minarets & domes.
detail_description: Gandhi Hall, originally known as King Edward Hall, is a historical building in Indore, India. Constructed in 1904, it showcases impressive Indo-Gothic architecture with elaborate windows, minarets, and domes. The facade is made of white marble and red stones and features a unique clock tower on all four sides. After India gained independence in 1947, the hall was renamed Gandhi Hall in honor of Mahatma Gandhi.
name: Gandhi Hall
address: 51, Mahatma Gandhi Rd, Shastri Market, New Siyaganj, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452007, India

detail_description: Regional Park Indore, also known as Pipliyapala Regional Park, is a sprawling recreational area located along the picturesque banks of Pipliyapala Lake. The park boasts stunning gardens such as the Mughal Garden and French Garden, adding to its allure. Visitors can enjoy activities like pedal-boating and motor-boating while taking in the enchanting Mist and Musical Fountain, French Gardens, Labyrinths, and Artist Village.
name: Regional Park Indore
address: Regional Park Rd, Kasturba Gram, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452020, India

excerpt: Indore is a city in west-central India. It’s known for the 7-story Rajwada Palace and the Lal Baag Palace, which date back to Indore’s 19th-century Holkar dynasty. The Holkar rulers are honored by a cluster of tombs and cenotaphs at Chhatri Baag. The night market Sarafa Bazar sells street food. East is the Indo-Gothic Gandhi Hall and clock tower. The Jain temple Kanch Mandir has a mirrored mosaic interior.
detail_description: Indore, a city in west-central India, is steeped in history and culture. The 19th-century Rajwada Palace and Lal Baag Palace showcase the grandeur of the Holkar dynasty, while Chhatri Baag pays homage to the rulers with its tombs and cenotaphs. Visitors can savor street food at Sarafa Bazar or admire the Indo-Gothic architecture of Gandhi Hall and clock tower.
name: Indore
address: Madhya Pradesh, India

excerpt: Prominent temple dedicated to the Hindu goddess of food featuring an ornate gate & elephant statues.
detail_description: The Annapurna Temple is an ornate Hindu temple in Indore, India dedicated to the goddess of food, Annapurna. Thousands of pilgrims and tourists visit this shrine every year, drawn by its imposing facade and gilded gate.
name: Shri Annapurna Temple, Indore
address: Annapurna Rd, Annapurna Mandir, Kranti Kriplani Nagar, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452009, India

excerpt: Cenotaphs from the late 1800s memorializing Holkar rulers with wall carvings & statues.
detail_description: Nestled along the serene banks of the Saraswati River, Krishna Pura Chhatri in Indore is a stunning cenotaph that pays homage to the Holkar rulers of the 19th century. This remarkable monument features intricate wall carvings and statues that reflect the grandeur of its time, making it one of Indore's most cherished landmarks. As you explore this architectural gem, you'll be captivated by its exquisite Gopuram Mandap, showcasing beautiful textures and symmetry.
name: Krishna Pura Chhatri, Indore
address: PV95+G66, Mahatma Gandhi Rd, Rajwada, Maharaja Tukoji Rao Holker Cloth Market, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452007, India

detail_description: Nehru Park, formerly known as Biscoe Park, is a popular attraction in Indore. It's not only a beautiful green space but also a haven for birdwatchers due to its fully-grown fig trees that attract various bird species. The park is also home to the Chidiya Ghar zoological park, where visitors can see exotic flora and fauna and even rare animals like the White Tigress with her cubs.
name: Nehru park
address: Saste Nagar, Nehru Park 2, Shivaji Nagar, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452001, India

name: Khajrana Temple Parking 2
address: 246, Ganeshpuri, Khajrana, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452016, India

excerpt: Family-friendly water park featuring a variety of slides & pools, plus picnic areas.
detail_description: The Crescent Water Park is one of the most popular water parks in Indore and offers a variety of slides and pools for guests to enjoy. It is easily accessible by road, making it perfect for families or friends who want to have a fun-filled day. The park charges an entry fee of just Rs. 499, making it affordable for everyone in the family.
name: Crescent Water Park, Indore
address: Gram Jamniya, Near Narmada Kshipra Devguradia Khurd, Kampel Rd, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452016, India

detail_description: Indore Zoo Park, also known as Kamla Nehru Prani Sangrahalaya, is a sprawling 51-acre wildlife sanctuary in the heart of the city. It houses a diverse array of over 57 animal species and approximately 628 specimens, including mammals, birds, and reptiles. The zoo's lush green environment attracts numerous visitors daily. Established in 1974 and expanded in 1999 to its current size, this wild wonderland offers an incredible adventure for all ages.
name: Indore Zoo Park
address: PV3H+P57, Doordarshan Kendra, Navlakha, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452001, India
